700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://fashionista.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEzMDkzMTU1ODA3OTYyNTc1/julia-roberts.jpg 380w, https://fashionista.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEzMDkzMTU1ODA3OTYyNTc1/julia-roberts.jpg 620w, https://fashionista.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEzMDkzMTU1ODA3OTYyNTc1/julia-roberts.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Julia Roberts and Kiefer Sutherland.\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://fashionista.com/.image/t_share/MjEzMDkzMTU1ODA3OTYyNTc1/julia-roberts.jpg\" data-src=\"https://fashionista.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEzMDkzMTU1ODA3OTYyNTc1/julia-roberts.jpg\" height=\"3000\" width=\"2287\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003eJulia Roberts and Kiefer Sutherland.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto: Ron Galella, Ltd./Ron Galella Collection via Getty Images\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThere are perfectly good celebrity style moments, and then there are the looks that really stick with you, the ones you try desperately to recreate at home. In \u0026#39;\u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/tag/great-outfits-in-fashion-history\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eGreat Outfits in Fashion History\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e,\u0026#39; Fashionista editors are revisiting their all-time favorite lewks.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIs this a safe space? Confession time: I\u0026#39;ve never seen \u0026#34;Pretty Woman\u0026#34; (or \u0026#34;Notting Hill,\u0026#34; but that\u0026#39;s a discussion for another time). You can now understand why my introduction to \u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/tag/julia-roberts\"\u003eJulia Roberts\u003c/a\u003e wasn\u0026#39;t from her \u0026#39;\u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/tag/90s\"\u003e90s\u003c/a\u003e films like most — it was through my obsession with scrolling through \u0026#34;Best Dressed\u0026#34; lists. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe all have a top \u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/2021/01/julia-roberts-golden-globes-1991-outfit\"\u003eRoberts \u0026#39;90s sartorial moment\u003c/a\u003e that lives in our heads rent-free. I\u0026#39;d bet my non-existent life savings that the first image to come to mind is her iconic \u003ca href=\"https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/julia-roberts-golden-globes-1990\" rel=\"noopener\" onclick=\"return phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eoversized Giorgio Armani suit\u003c/a\u003e at the 1990 \u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/tag/golden-globes\"\u003eGolden Globes\u003c/a\u003e. It\u0026#39;s certainly at the forefront of \u003cem\u003emy\u003c/em\u003e brain when I think of Roberts\u0026#39; red-carpet history. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBut if I were to point to honorary mentions, the actor\u0026#39;s appearance at the 1991 \u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/tag/oscars\"\u003eOscars\u003c/a\u003e deserves its flowers. For the occasion, while she opted against a suit, she couldn\u0026#39;t help but reach for something tailored, wearing a structured evening dress by Richard Tyler. The full-length number was a feminine take on a man\u0026#39;s tailcoat, featuring a funnel neckline, subtle power shoulders, loop-and-button front closures and high side slits with silk chiffon under panels. \u003c/p\u003e\u003csection id=\"phx-3\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eScroll to Continue\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"phx-5\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"2\"\u003eRecommended Articles\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003